<TITLE> Door-to-door vaccination coverage up to 14th </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Jan 10(bdnews24.com)--Vaccination centres remained open until 8:00pm on the country's 18th National Vaccination Day on Sunday and will remain open through the night for urgent cases. Volunteers will also conduct a door-to-door campaign from Jan 11-14 to cover those who miss out. With a target of immunising 2.2 crore children from polio, 600,000 volunteers worked at 1.40 lakh centres across the country where children were also administered vitamin A and deworming tablets besides the polio vaccine. Polio vaccine (two drops) was given to children below five years of age. Children between the ages of 1 year and 5 years were given a vitamin A capsule and those between 2 and 5 a deworming tablet. Children between 9 months and 5 years will given measles vaccine from Feb 14 to 28. Parents have been cautioned at a press conference that children should not be given vaccines on empty stomach. bdnew
